Hello all-

We have upgraded EndlessForms.com <http://EndlessForms.com>  so you can now
3D print the objects you evolve. The options are incredible: you can print
in everything from silver and steel to hard plastic or soft rubber. You can
also download the file that describes the object or post it on Thingiverse,
an online repository of 3D files. Just click on any organism and you'll see
the buttons (e.g. "3D Print").

We've also enabled users to view the ancestral lineage of newly evolved
organisms, such as this one:

http://endlessforms.com/o/132606

We are holding a weekly competition, where the highest rated organism
published by a registered user will be 3D printed in plastic and sent to
them. If you are interested in holding a piece of the future, submit a few
entries!

Last weeks winner actually was Ken Stanley, with this amazing submission.
Congrats Ken!

http://endlessforms.com/o/126307

As Ken said, the site will get better the more people use it. So please help
spread the word. We've made that easier by adding Facebook & Twitter
buttons. 

Are there any other features you would like see?


Best regards,
Jeff Clune

Postdoctoral Fellow
Hod Lipson's Creative Machines Laboratory
Cornell University
jeffclune@...
www.msu.edu/~jclune



--B_3391253548_14978080
